    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen coding a project with many files, often we make multiple changes in different files, and want to undo them all, and want the editor to remember which files we made the changes to and in which order. Most GUI editors seem to support this, and it becomes especially useful when using LSP actions that might affect dozens of files at the same time (e.g. a symbol rename action that changes all the files where this symbol appeared. It is hard to find each affected file by hand and undo them one by one).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSome way to make nvim track undo history across an entire workspace, and undo all changes in this workspace in the order they are made. \n\nIt seems that this is already possible if we write a plugin (e.g. modify `undo-tree` or `fundo` plugins to cover an entire workspace), but I still think it's worth writing this issue to see if a PR might be welcome in nvim itself, or if I missed existing plugins that already achieve this.\n\nThank you!",
